            <nav class="breadcrumb" role="navigation"><h2 class="element-invisible">You are here</h2><ol><li><a href="/">Home</a> › </li><li><a href="/resources" title="Resources for the diocese">Resources</a> › </li></ol></nav>      <a id="main-content"></a>
                    <h1 class="title" id="page-title">Diocesan Archives</h1>
                                          


<article class="node-306 node node-page view-mode-full clearfix">

  
  <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p><strong><a href="http://diocesanarchivesbc.com" target="_blank">Archives of the Anglican Diocese of British Columbia - </a></strong><a href="http://diocesanarchivesbc.com/">http://diocesanarchivesbc.com</a><strong> </strong></p>
<p>The Archives provides the Diocese with a memory and is a reflection of the true face of the organization that created it.</p>
<p>The task of the Diocesan Archives is to collect, protect, and provide access to the records of the Diocese including its Bishops, officers, clergy, parishes, and related organizations, as laid down in the Canons of the Diocese. The Archives also collects private records of relevance to the life of the Diocese.</p>
<p>From 1859 to 1879 the Diocese of British Columbia included all of what is today the Province of British Columbia. In 1879 the Province was divided into three diocese; Caledonia, New Westminster, and British Columbia. The Anglican Diocese of British Columbia now comprises Vancouver Island and adjacent islands.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>The Diocesan Archives will be closed for the Summer months of July and August,  2015. We take this annual hiatus in order to address collection backlog and conservation. We will continue to monitor both email and phone messages and we will respond to any <span class="caps">URGENT</span> request for documents within 5 business days. The Archives doors will re-open on Tuesday, September 1, 2015 at 10:00 am.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Please be assured that staff will be in the building throughout the closure period, generally on Thursday and Friday, should the parishes need support in any way. "</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Jacquie Nevins, Archivist<br />
	Anglican Diocese of British Columbia Archives<br />
	900 Vancouver Street<br />
	Victoria, <span class="caps">BC</span><br /><a href="250-386-7781">250-386-7781</a> Ext. 253</p>
<p> </p>
</div></div></div>
  
  
</article><!-- /.node -->
